 # Design: types-and-helpers
 
-> This document is the Change Design — written after proposal approval, describing how to implement. Each section has fill-in guidance. After this document, proceed to task breakdown.
+> Change c1 of ph.2-core-engine — type foundation + first pure helpers (`coordKey`, `winCheck`, `createInitialState`). Prerequisite for c2 (move+history) and c3 (reducer).
 
 ---
 
 ## Context & Goals
 
-<!--
-1. Briefly describe context — what constraints exist?
-2. Core design goals (no more than 3)
-3. Must align with proposal Intent and Must-haves
--->
-
-{{background-and-goals}}
+- **Context**: ph.1 left `src/types.ts` with `Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`, `Intent`. The reducer (c3) needs `Level`, `GameState`, `HistoryEntry`, `AnimSpec`. `winCheck` needs `coordKey` because `Set<Coord>` uses object identity and pushed boxes are fresh objects (research P1, pitfalls #15). `createInitialState` is the factory c3's reducer and ph.3's loader call. Locked decisions D1–D10 (context.md) apply; this change touches D2 (types), D3 (immutable GameState), D4 (winCheck O(B)), D8 (AnimSpec), D9 (boxes array), D10 (tests under `tests/unit/core/`, node env).
+- **Goals**: (1) Export the four new types without modifying existing exports. (2) Ship `coordKey` + `winCheck` + `createInitialState` as pure, DOM-free functions. (3) Lay the `initial` snapshot on `GameState` so c3's pure 2-arg `reducer` can `reset` without a closure (research P6).
+- **Aligns with**: proposal Must-haves #1–#7; research.md signatures (verified 2026-07-01).
 
