 ### Core Data Structures
-
-<!--
-Key types/interfaces/data structures introduced or modified by this design.
-Use TypeScript interface format. Brief description per type.
--->
-
-{{data-structures}}
-
+```ts
+export interface Level { id: string; width: number; height: number;
+  walls: Set<Coord>; targets: Set<Coord>; player: Coord; boxes: Coord[]; }
+export interface GameState { levelId: string;
+  static: { width: number; height: number; walls: Set<Coord>; targets: Set<Coord>; };
+  initial: { player: Coord; boxes: Coord[] };   // immutable snapshot for reset (P6)
+  player: Coord; boxes: Coord[]; moveCount: number; history: HistoryEntry[]; won: boolean; }
+export interface HistoryEntry { player: Coord; pushedBoxIndex?: number; boxFrom?: Coord; moveCount: number; }
+export interface AnimSpec { from: Coord; to: Coord; duration: number; entities: ('player' | number)[]; }
+```
+`static` and `initial` are shared by reference across all reducer outputs and MUST NOT be mutated (D3, research P3). `won` is recomputed by `winCheck` on every transition (D4).
 ### Data Flow
 
