+# wincheck — Delta Spec
+
+> Behavioral contract for `winCheck(state: GameState): boolean` introduced in change c1 (types-and-helpers), ph.2-core-engine.
+> Source: design.md, research.md (Win-check algorithm, P1), context.md D4, architecture.md "Win-check algorithm".
+
+---
+
+## ADDED Requirements
+
+### Requirement: Win condition is all-boxes-on-targets
+
+The system SHALL report `won: true` if and only if every box occupies a target tile. The check MUST be a pure function of `state.boxes` and `state.static.targets` with no side effects and no dependency on `moveCount`, `history`, or `player`.
+
+> Confidence: HIGH | Source: context.md D4, architecture.md "Win-check algorithm", research.md `winCheck` signature
+
+#### Scenario: all boxes on targets (structural equality via coordKey)
+
+- **GIVEN** a `GameState` whose `boxes` are structurally equal to `static.targets` but referentially distinct objects (e.g. boxes `[{1,1},{3,3}]`, targets `{{1,1},{3,3}}` built from separate object literals)
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called
+- **THEN** it returns `true`, proving the `coordKey` reconciliation defeats `Set<Coord>` object identity (pitfall P1)
+
+#### Scenario: one box off target
+
+- **GIVEN** `boxes = [{1,1},{3,3}]` and `static.targets = {{1,1},{5,5}}` (one box not on a target)
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called
+- **THEN** it returns `false`
+
+#### Scenario: box count differs from target count
+
+- **GIVEN** `boxes = [{1,1}]` and `static.targets = {{1,1},{3,3}}` (1 box, 2 targets)
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called
+- **THEN** it returns `false` without iterating boxes (short-circuit on `boxes.length !== targets.size`)
+
+#### Scenario: empty boxes and empty targets (degenerate level)
+
+- **GIVEN** `boxes = []` and `static.targets` of size 0
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called
+- **THEN** it returns `true` (vacuously all boxes are on targets; defined behavior for a no-box level)
+
+---
+
+### Requirement: Structural membership via coordKey, not Set#has
+
+The system SHALL NOT test box-on-target membership with `Set<Coord>#has` (which uses object identity). It MUST build a `Set<string>` of `coordKey(target)` from `state.static.targets` and test `coordKey(box)` membership against it. The `state.static.targets` set MUST NOT be mutated during the check.
+
+> Confidence: HIGH | Source: research.md P1, design.md "Data Flow"
+
+#### Scenario: freshly pushed box on a target is detected
+
+- **GIVEN** a box that was just pushed onto a target — a freshly allocated `Coord` object structurally equal to a target but a different reference than any object in `static.targets`
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called
+- **THEN** it returns `true` (the fresh object is matched by `coordKey`, not by reference)
+
+#### Scenario: static.targets is not mutated by the check
+
+- **GIVEN** a `GameState` with a known `static.targets` set
+- **WHEN** `winCheck(state)` is called any number of times
+- **THEN** `state.static.targets` is unchanged (same size, same entries, same reference) — `winCheck` only reads `static`
+
+---
+
+### Requirement: O(B + T) cost, no incremental tracking
+
+The system SHALL compute the win state on every call in O(B + T) time where B = `boxes.length` and T = `targets.size`. It MUST NOT maintain an incremental "boxes-on-target" counter in `GameState`; the single source of truth is the per-call check.
+
+> Confidence: HIGH | Source: architecture.md "Win-check algorithm", research.md `winCheck` signature
+
+#### Scenario: recomputed on every transition
+
+- **GIVEN** a `won: true` state and a subsequent `undo` that removes a box from its target
+- **WHEN** `winCheck` is re-run on the undone state (by c3's reducer)
+- **THEN** it returns `false` (the flag is always derived, never stale — pitfall BLOCKER #3 / MAJOR #17 mitigation)
+
+---
+
+### Requirement: Pure and DOM-free
+
+The `winCheck` module MUST be a pure function importable in the node-env `unit` Vitest project with zero DOM setup. It MUST NOT import from `render/`, `input/`, `anim/`, `dom`, or `storage`. It MUST NOT allocate anything beyond the per-call `Set<string>` of target keys.
+
+> Confidence: HIGH | Source: context.md D1/D10, proposal Must-have #6
+
+#### Scenario: no DOM imports in src/core/
+
+- **GIVEN** the `src/core/winCheck.ts` source file
+- **WHEN** scanned for `dom`, `canvas`, `window`, or `document` imports
+- **THEN** no matches are found and the file runs under `vitest run` (unit project, node env) without a DOM harness
